  "name": "Trend Following ADX HMA Strategy",
  "description": "This algorithm utilizes a combination of the 14-period Average Directional Movement Index (ADX) and the 20-period Hull Moving Average (HMA) to identify trend-following opportunities. Long entries are triggered when the ADX exceeds 25 and the closing price crosses above the HMA, while short entries are activated under similar ADX conditions with a downward price crossover.",
  "algorithm_type": "TrendFollowing",
  "prompt": "Design an intermediate-level TrendFollowing trading algorithm in Python that uses the combination of a 14-period Average Directional Movement Index (ADX) and 20-period Hull Moving Average (HMA) on 1-hour candles. The system should generate a long entry when the 14-period ADX is above 25, and the closing price crosses above the 20-period HMA. Short entry is triggered when the ADX is above 25 and price crosses below the HMA. Exits occur when a cross in the opposite direction happens or if ADX drops below 20. The algorithm should include a function to calculate the ADX and HMA, and output trade signals (\"long\", \"short\", \"exit\") for each data point.",
